~*~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Chloe walked into her father’s office and gave the secretary one of her beaming smiles.  The older woman smiled back at her.<br>
<br>
“Hi Kathy,” Chloe greeted cheerfully as she swung her key ring around on her finger.  “Is he ready yet?”  Kathy shook her head.<br>
<br>
“Sorry sweetie, he’s not here,” she answered.  Chloe’s smile fell.<br>
<br>
“His car is in the shop and I was supposed to pick him up.  He could have at least called me and let me know that I didn’t need to drive all the way out here,” Chloe rambled.  Kathy chuckled.<br>
<br>
“I meant he’s not in his office,” she clarified.  Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“I knew that,” she said.  <br>
<br>
“He was called down to lab seven, something about one of the vats leaking,” Kathy said.  “But you’re welcome to wait here if you want.”  Chloe seemed to think about it and then shook her head.<br>
<br>
“No thanks.  I’m a little hungry.  Can you tell me where the vending machines are?”  She asked.  Kathy went back to her typing.<br>
<br>
“Down the hall and take a left,” she said without raising her head from the computer screen.  Chloe turned around to head out the door and paused when Kathy spoke again.  “Chloe?”<br>
<br>
“Yeah?”<br>
<br>
“Don’t let your father catch you snooping around down there,” Kathy said, knowing full well that Chloe couldn’t pass up the urge to find out about the vat leak.  Chloe bit her lip as she smiled.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know what you’re talking about,” she replied in a faux innocent voice.  Kathy grinned and kept typing as Chloe walked away.  ‘Hmm, maybe I should have gotten directions,’ Chloe mused as she tried to make her way through the labyrinth of hallways.  She smiled when she saw a sign next to a door indicating that it was the entrance to lab seven, but the smile quickly fell when she saw that it had a keycard and pad entry lock.  “Damn,” she mumbled.  As if by divine intervention, at least in Chloe’s mind, the door opened and one of the employees came walking through.  She stuck out her hand to keep the door from closing.  The older man smiled at her briefly and she smiled back.  <br>
<br>
He turned and walked down the hallway, paying her virtually no regard.  Chloe tried to keep herself from laughing.  Security controls were a good thing if the employees actually enforced them and an even better thing for her when they didn’t.  She stepped into the lab and took a quick look around.  She guessed that the small group of people huddled around a vat was probably where the spill was, especially since she could see Gabe and Lex standing with them.  Lex looked out of place wearing his expensive suit and no lab jacket, but she figured that he rarely spent time in that section of the plant.  She began to walk over there, disregarding the warning signs that said safety gloves and hats must be worn at all times in that area.  Gabe spotted her and gave her a small wave.<br>
<br>
“Hey sweetheart,” he said as she walked up to him.  Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“Hi Dad,” she replied.  “Mr. Luthor,” she said with a nod of her head.<br>
<br>
“Miss Sullivan,” Lex greeted.  “What brings you to lab seven?”  He didn’t look pleased that she was there.  The last thing he needed was for her to do an article on the vat leak and end up having the EPA shut them down for a while.  She shrugged as if it was no big deal.<br>
<br>
“Kathy said that Dad was down here, and I’m picking him up from work today,” Chloe answered.  Lex looked at her with suspicion, but accepted the excuse.  Chloe turned to Gabe.  “So are you ready yet?”  Her dad frowned and looked at the floor, where a new puddle of the liquid from the vat was starting to form.<br>
<br>
“I’m afraid not,” he said with a shake of his head.  “Go ahead and go home.  I’ll just catch a ride with someone from the plant.”  Chloe crossed her arms.<br>
<br>
“And you couldn’t have told me this *before* I drove all the way out here?”  She asked with mock anger.  Gabe grinned.<br>
<br>
“Sorry sweetheart,” he said.  Chloe shrugged.  <br>
<br>
“No problem,” she said.  “See you when you get home.”  Chloe hadn’t noticed that the puddle extended to where she was and when she turned to walk away, she slipped and fell.  “Yuck!”  The liquid was filmy and now covering her posterior and her hands.  “What is this stuff?”  <br>
<br>
“I’d tell you, but I’m pretty sure you don’t want to know,” Gabe answered.  Chloe made a disgusted face.  She noticed that a couple of the small meteor rocks she had in her bag had fallen out and were now covered in film as well.  <br>
<br>
“As long as it comes off,” she said.  On instinct, Lex reached out his hand to help her up, not paying attention to the fact that neither one of them was wearing gloves.  Chloe picked up the rocks and then took Lex’s hand with her free hand.  They yanked their hands away from each other after she was standing.  “It’s burning!”  Lex frowned at his now goop covered hand.<br>
<br>
“You’re right,” he said with displeasure.  “We’d better get to clean up.”  Chloe nodded in agreement and dropped the rocks back into her bag.  Gabe gave them a sympathetic grin.<br>
<br>
“At least we know that it’s not toxic,” he called at them as they were walking toward the clean up area.  “You should be fine.”  Chloe rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“That’s really comforting,” she said sarcastically.  Lex chuckled and then noticed that she was looking down at her hands.  <br>
<br>
“Still hurts?”  He asked.  Chloe frowned.<br>
<br>
“A little, but it seems to be going away,” she said.  “You?”<br>
<br>
“The same,” Lex said.  He got a small smirk on his face as they finally reached the sinks.  “So your Dad calls you sweetheart?”  He teased.  She shot him a glare out of the corner of her eye as they both pumped some liquid sanitizer onto her hands and ran them under the water.<br>
<br>
“Your Dad doesn’t call you sweetheart?”  She bit back.  Lex laughed loudly.<br>
<br>
“No,” he answered.  “But my Mom used to call me ‘dumpling’.”  Chloe laughed and smiled at him.<br>
<br>
“I’ll have to remember that,” she said.<br>
<br>
“Please don’t,” Lex said seriously.  Chloe looked at her hands after drying them off.  They were a little red, as if the top layer of skin had been burned off.  She frowned and held them up for Lex to see.<br>
<br>
“Is your hand red?”  She asked.  He looked down at his own hand.<br>
<br>
“A little, but I’m sure it’ll be fine.  At least it’s only one of my hands,” he said with a small smirk.  Chloe gave him a forced grin and turned to leave.<br>
<br>
“Whatever you say *dumpling*,” she threw over her shoulder.  Lex cringed.  He knew he shouldn’t have told her that.<br>
<br>
Chloe waved goodbye to her dad and left to go home.  The drive home was long and boring as usual, and Chloe started to daydream as she drove down the back roads.  She told herself a million times that she was over Clark and that she had to stop thinking of him like that, but a few little fantasies weren’t going to hurt anyone, right?  An image flitted through her mind of she and Clark making love and she smiled to herself as she pulled up in her driveway.  Lex Luthor had a very different reaction.  He was talking to Gabe and suddenly Chloe’s daydream appeared in his mind.  He smiled inwardly at the image of Chloe being naked, but then saw Clark and he shook his head to try and clear the picture from his mind.<br>
<br>
‘What the hell was that?!’  He thought to himself.  Chloe furrowed her brow and looked around the room.  She could have sworn she heard a man’s voice.<br>
<br>
‘What the hell was what?’  She thought to herself as she kept looking for the man who she knew had to be there.  Lex paled when he recognized Chloe’s voice in his head.<br>
<br>
‘Chloe?’  He thought.<br>
<br>
“Yeah, I’m right here,” Chloe said aloud.  “Where are you?  And more importantly, *who* are you, and what are you doing in my house?”  Lex cringed, but did his best to compose himself.<br>
<br>
“Gabe, I’m not feeling too well,” he said.  “I’m going home.  Can you handle this?”  Gabe grinned and nodded.<br>
<br>
“No problem.”<br>
<br>
‘Gabe?’ Chloe thought.  “My Dad’s at work,” she said to the air, hoping that the man would come out of hiding.<br>
<br>
‘I’m at work too Chloe,’ Lex thought.  ‘I think something happened to us.’  Chloe’s eyes grew wide when she finally recognized Lex’s voice, and realized that it was coming from within her own head.<br>
<br>
‘Well fix it!’  She mentally yelled.  <br>
<br>
‘I’m on my way home now,’ Lex said.  ‘I have the files on the chemical back at the house.’<br>
<br>
‘Speed!  I can’t have your voice inside my head Lex!’  She said.  Lex pursed his lips, knowing that he would regret his next sentence.<br>
<br>
‘It’s not just our voices,’ Lex thought.  <br>
<br>
‘What do you mean?’  Chloe made her way to the refrigerator and took out a small container of hot fudge topping.  Her mind drifted to less than chaste thoughts of what she could be doing with Clark and the chocolate and Lex yelled at her.<br>
<br>
“Stop it!”  He practically screamed.  Chloe furrowed her brow.<br>
<br>
‘Stop what?  I was just fixing myself some ice cream,’ she thought.<br>
<br>
‘Stop fantasizing about you and Clark!’  Lex ordered.  ‘Don’t get me wrong, the images of you are terrific, but I have no desire to see you having sex with another man.’  Chloe choked on the ice cream she just tried to swallow.  A furious blush rose to her cheeks.<br>
<br>
‘You – you ---’<br>
<br>
‘Saw it.  Yes.  I told you, it’s not just our voices,’ Lex thought.  <br>
<br>
“Oh God,” Chloe groaned in embarrassment.<br>
<br>
‘Just try and control yourself, don’t let it happen again,’ Lex told her.  Chloe’s mouth opened a little.  How dare he tell her what to think or not to think?<br>
<br>
‘What’s the matter?’  She asked.  ‘Jealous that it wasn’t you?’  Lex squared his jaw.<br>
<br>
‘Don’t be ridiculous, I ---’ Lex’s thoughts drifted to a vivid image of he and Chloe making love on his bed.  They were sweaty and writhing against each other with full passion.  Chloe screamed her release and Lex tried to clear his thoughts.<br>
<br>
“What the hell was that?!”  Chloe yelled.  Lex ran his hand around the back of his neck.<br>
<br>
“Don’t get mad at me, you’re the one who suggested it,” Lex said.  He frowned when he realized that he was arguing with her aloud even though she wasn’t there.<br>
<br>
‘I – argh!  Just find a way to fix it!  And no more thinking about – you know – for either of us.  Deal?’<br>
<br>
‘Deal,’ Lex thought.  He immediately regretted thinking it.  He was certain now that he had an imprint of the two of them in that position in his mind that he would want to think about it frequently.  He imagined himself kissing her passionately, their tongues maneuvering against each other in an erotic dance; him moving his hands under her shirt and ---<br>
<br>
“Knock it off!”  Chloe yelled.  Lex snapped out of his thoughts.<br>
<br>
‘Sorry,’ he thought.  A small smirk crossed his lips.  <br>
<br>
“Knock what off?”  Lana asked in confusion as she walked into the house.  Chloe turned around to face her and offered her a nervous smile.<br>
<br>
“Nothing, nothing’s wrong,” Chloe lied.<br>
<br>
‘Who are you talking to?’  Lex asked.<br>
<br>
‘Lana just got home,’ Chloe explained.  She thought she heard Lex snicker and shook her head.  “How was work?”<br>
<br>
“Fine,” Lana said.  “Kind of busy.  But you’ll never guess what happened!”  Lana seemed excited and Chloe sat down next to her.  <br>
<br>
“What happened?”  Chloe asked.<br>
<br>
‘What happened?’  Lex asked.<br>
<br>
‘Shut up,’ Chloe thought.  ‘I’m talking to Lana.’<br>
<br>
“Okay, you know Damian Thomas?”  Lana asked excitedly.  Chloe nodded.  “I think he likes you.  He was asking all these questions about you, like if you were seeing anybody and stuff.”<br>
<br>
“Really?”  Chloe asked.  Lana nodded happily.<br>
<br>
“So what do you think?  You want me to try and hook you two up?”  She asked.<br>
<br>
‘Would you please tell me what’s going on?’  Lex asked.  ‘And who the guy is?’  Chloe ignored him.<br>
<br>
“I – uh – maybe,” Chloe said.  Lana rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Okay, well think about it and let me know,” she said.  Chloe nodded and buried her head in her hands after Lana left the room.<br>
<br>
‘Thinking about it is the last thing I should do,’ Chloe thought to herself.<br>
<br>
‘Thinking about what?’  Lex asked.<br>
<br>
‘God!  You’re nosier than I am,’ she thought.  Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
‘It’s a little hard not to be when we share each other’s thoughts,’ he replied.<br>
<br>
‘I guess that’s a valid point,’ Chloe conceded.<br>
<br>
‘So are you going to tell me what’s going on?’  He asked.<br>
<br>
‘Lana thinks some guy – the guy in the mental picture – likes me and wants to try and set us up on a date,’ Chloe said.  Lex was silent for a minute and Chloe got her hopes up that maybe their connection had worn off.<br>
<br>
‘I don’t think it would be a good idea for either of us to date until we have this sorted out,’ Lex said.  Chloe frowned.<br>
<br>
‘I’m not going to give up the little social life I have just so you won’t feel uncomfortable,’ Chloe thought.  Lex pictured them making love again.  The image was strong and Chloe could feel herself becoming aroused at the very thought of it.  ‘Okay, stop it!  You made your point.’<br>
<br>
‘Thank you.’<br>
<br>
‘Whatever,’ Chloe thought shortly.  ‘Just look over your files and see if there’s anything we can do to reverse this.’<br>
<br>
‘Of course *sweetheart*,’ Lex replied.  <br>
<br>
‘Bastard.’<br>
<br>
‘You can call me anything you’d like, as long as it keeps images of you with teenage boys out of my head,’ Lex quipped.<br>
<br>
‘Fine.  *Dumpling*.’<br>
