<br>
“I think Clark must have been in an accident,” he said.  Chloe and Lana’s eyes both widened.<br>
<br>
“What?  When did this happen?”  Lana asked.<br>
<br>
“Is he okay?”  Chloe asked.  <br>
<br>
“No, no.  I just meant ---” Gabe trailed off and sighed again.  “The reason he gave for you two to need to go to the lab was a little out there.”  Lana looked at Chloe.<br>
<br>
“You had to go to a lab?  Why?”  She asked, suddenly feeling guilty that she had automatically jumped to the conclusion that Clark was interested in her friend.<br>
<br>
“We didn’t even make it there,” Chloe said.<br>
<br>
“Car trouble,” Lex said.  Gabe arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“Uh-huh,” he said.  “So, why don’t you tell me why you were really going there?”  He asked Lex.  “Did Chloe con you into getting information for a story or something?”  Chloe fought hard to keep the color from rising to her cheeks.<br>
<br>
‘Or something,’ Lex thought suggestively.<br>
<br>
‘Don’t start,’ Chloe warned.  Gabe saw the way Chloe and Lex were looking at each other but not speaking and he frowned.<br>
<br>
“Something I should know?”  He asked.  Chloe turned to him.<br>
<br>
“What did Clark tell you?”  She asked hesitantly.  Gabe let out a light chuckle.  ‘That’s a good sign.  He probably didn’t tell my dad about what happened.’<br>
<br>
‘Agreed,’ Lex thought.  <br>
<br>
“He said that because of the chemical spill at the plant that you two can read each other’s minds now,” Gabe said, still chuckling, as if the very idea was completely absurd.  Lana smiled brightly.<br>
<br>
“That’s ridiculous,” she said.  “Why would Clark say something like that?”  Chloe and Lex looked at each other again and then back to Gabe.  Gabe’s face dropped the second they looked back at him.  <br>
<br>
“Oh, no,” he said under his breath.  <br>
<br>
“You’re kidding?”  Lana asked in astonishment.  Chloe and Lex both shook their heads.  Gabe looked up from the floor at them and shook his head at Lex.  <br>
<br>
“God, I’m so sorry, Lex.”  <br>
<br>
‘Why do I have a feeling that he wouldn’t be apologizing to you if he knew the whole story?’  Chloe thought.  Lex inwardly laughed.<br>
<br>
‘Not only can we read each other’s minds, but I also took advantage of the fact to take your daughter’s virginity,’ he thought dryly.  ‘Yeah, I’m pretty sure that wouldn’t go over very well.’  Chloe giggled and Gabe and Lana gave her a strange look.  <br>
<br>
“Sorry,” she mumbled.  <br>
<br>
“So how do we fix it?”  Gabe asked.  Lex was still looking at Chloe when he answered Gabe’s question.<br>
<br>
“Fix what?”  He asked absently.  Lex felt Gabe’s eyes boring a hole into the side of his head and he turned around.  “Oh, the situation,” he said.  “I have no idea.  Like I said, we never made it to the lab.”<br>
<br>
“But you can go there tomorrow, right?”  Gabe asked.<br>
<br>
