<br>
‘Shut up,’ Chloe thought.<br>
<br>
‘Chloe.’<br>
<br>
‘No,’ she thought.  ‘I’ll stand my ground so I don’t embarrass myself in front of my dad and Lana.’  Unfortunately, her body had other ideas.  An image flitted into her mind of when they were in the car together and her mind started to expand on the memory.  Lex’s eyes grew wide as he felt the arousal start to warm his body.  Chloe was able to snap out of it just long enough to fake a smile at Gabe and Lana.  “I’m not feeling too good, so I’m going to go upstairs and lie down.  Bye Lex.”  She practically ran up the stairs and Gabe furrowed his brow at his daughter’s retreating form.  Lana grimaced and leaned toward Gabe.<br>
<br>
“She, um, started her time of the month early,” she whispered.  Gabe’s mouth dropped open and he nodded in understanding.<br>
<br>
“Right,” he said and turned to Lex, who now looked flushed as well.  He frowned.  “You’re not looking well either Lex.”<br>
<br>
“I should go,” Lex said.  “I’ll talk to you later.”  He hurried out the door and Lana turned to Gabe.<br>
<br>
“Maybe it’s another side effect of the chemical spill,” she suggested.<br>
<br>
“Great,” Gabe said sarcastically.  “So not only can my daughter and my boss read each other’s minds, but they’re both sick too.”<br>
