<br>
‘No, thank God,’ he answered.  ‘It’s hard enough for me to handle you thinking about Clark without feeling the emotions behind it.’<br>
<br>
Chloe laughed loudly, and because she was still staring longingly at her car, she didn’t notice that Clark had opened the door and was leaning against the door frame with a lopsided boyish grin on his face.<br>
<br>
“Should I ask?”  Clark asked in amusement.  Chloe’s head whipped around and her face colored quickly.  She smiled with embarrassment at him.<br>
<br>
“It’s nothing,” she lied and shook her head.  She glanced back at the driveway area.  “Lana and Pete aren’t here yet?”<br>
<br>
‘Oh, great,’ Lex thought sarcastically.<br>
<br>
‘I’m sure they’re just late.’<br>
<br>
‘I’m sure they’re not coming,’ Lex countered.  ‘Why would he give up spending time alone with you when he doesn’t have to?’<br>
<br>
‘For the millionth time, Clark Kent doesn’t see me like that.  Will you just stop it?  Geez!  If I didn’t know it was because you found my daydreams disturbing, then I’d say you sound like a jealous boyfriend,’ Chloe thought.  Clark cleared his throat and crossed his arms, but kept the grin on his face.<br>
<br>
“Trying to talk him into helping us study for history?”  Clark asked.  <br>
<br>
“Something like that,” Chloe said.  Clark’s grin turned into a smile that almost made her melt.  He stood to the side of the door and motioned for her to come inside.<br>
<br>
“Lana called.  One of her waitresses called in sick, so she had to go into work after all,” Clark said.<br>
<br>
“I thought they were closed on Sundays?”<br>
<br>
“They have been, but profits haven’t been as good as Lana was hoping for the last couple of months, so she’s trying out being open for shorter hours on Sundays.”<br>
<br>
“Oh,” Chloe said.  ‘Why didn’t you tell me that?’<br>
<br>
‘Why didn’t I tell you *what*?’<br>
<br>
‘Lana’s trying out having the Talon open for limited hours on Sundays,’ Chloe thought.<br>
<br>
‘I don’t know anything about it,’ Lex admitted.  ‘But, that’s good.  Even with the different things she’s been trying, nothing beats an after-church crowd.’  Chloe didn’t know what to think.  She understood his reasoning since he owned half of the Talon, but she was a little surprised that he didn’t mind Lana not being at Clark’s to keep an eye on them.  ‘Is Pete still coming?’  And there it was.  Lex thought Pete wouldn’t let anything happen between her and Clark.<br>
<br>
