<br>
“I won’t bother asking how you heard about that, but rest assured, it’s been taken care of,” he said as calmly as possible.  One corner of Lionel’s mouth curled upward.<br>
<br>
“Of course it has.  I wasn’t doubting your competence, *son*,” Lionel responded.  <br>
<br>
‘Yeah, right,’ Lex thought and then pursed his lips.  “Then the question still remains to be answered.”  ‘You might get your chance to ask that question of yours if he keeps stalling like this.’<br>
<br>
‘Really?’<br>
<br>
‘Sure.  Why not?  It’s not like I can make him dislike me anymore than he already does,’ Lex thought.<br>
<br>
‘I’m sorry,’ she thought sympathetically.<br>
<br>
‘Don’t worry about it.’  Lex stared straight at his father, his eye contact never wavering as he spoke to Chloe inside his head.  “It’s not like you to be at a loss for words, Dad.”  <br>
<br>
“Just paying a friendly visit to see my son, Lex.  Isn’t that allowed?”  Lionel said with a smirk.  Lex pursed his lips.  His patience with Lionel and his cryptic lies had completely run out.  It was time to do something about it.<br>
<br>
‘What’s your question Chloe?’  Lex thought.  <br>
<br>
“Woo-hoo!”  She yelled, earning her a puzzled expression from Clark.  She smiled at him, but concentrated on Lex.  ‘Ask him if his visit to Smallville has anything to do with Ted Dobson and Axis Chemicals.’  Lex arched an eyebrow and leaned back in his chair with confidence.<br>
<br>
“It might be if I thought for a minute that you were actually here to see me, but I have a feeling it has more to do with Axis Chemicals and Ted Dobson,” Lex said.<br>
<br>
‘That wasn’t a question,’ Chloe protested.<br>
<br>
‘He wouldn’t have answered a question straight out Chloe.’<br>
<br>
