<br>
“You’re treading on dangerous ground Lex,” he said in what almost sounded like a growl.  “Watch your step.”  He turned on his heel and left the room, leaving Lex with a broad smile on his face.  <br>
<br>
‘I owe you for that one Chloe.’<br>
<br>
‘Why?  What happened?’<br>
<br>
‘He threatened me and then hurried out of the room,’ Lex thought with a chuckle.  Chloe furrowed her brow.<br>
<br>
‘How is that a good thing?’<br>
<br>
‘You don’t know my father.  Trust me.  Having the upper hand is always good,’ Lex thought.  ‘So, why don’t we meet and you can tell me everything you know about Dobson and Axis Chemicals?’<br>
<br>
