<br>
‘Right.  The history test.’<br>
<br>
‘Quiz,’ Chloe corrected.<br>
<br>
‘When is this quiz supposed to take place?’  Lex asked.<br>
<br>
‘Tomorrow.’<br>
<br>
‘Ah.  And therein lies the reason that you’re studying today.’<br>
<br>
‘Very clever,’ she thought teasingly.<br>
<br>
‘You do realize that you’re not even going to be at school tomorrow, don’t you?’<br>
<br>
‘What?’<br>
<br>
‘Or have you forgotten about our appointment at the lab first thing in the morning?’  Lex thought.  Chloe’s eyes widened.<br>
<br>
“I can’t believe I forgot about that!”<br>
<br>
“Forgot about what?”  Clark asked.  Chloe stood up, gathering her books as she did so.  She shot Clark an apologetic smile.<br>
<br>
“Sorry Clark, but I completely forgot that I’m going to be at the lab tomorrow; for – you know,” she sort of explained.  Clark’s eyebrows rose.<br>
