“I don’t know,” Clark said.  “Maybe their hormones are being affected or something.  But you should have seen it, it was ---”<br>
<br>
“Clark, no offense, but I really don’t need that mental image right now,” Lana said.  ‘Or ever,’ she thought.  Clark blushed. <br>
<br>
“Yeah, sorry.”<br>
<br>
“So, she’s not there and she’s not home yet – do you think she’s with Lex?”  Lana asked in a now hushed voice.  Clark furrowed his brow until he realized that Chloe’s dad must be nearby.  <br>
<br>
“Maybe.  You think I should call over there?”<br>
<br>
“Do you think you could borrow the truck to drive over there?”  Lana asked.  “If  they’re as affected as you say they are, you might need to – break them apart or something, you know, before they do anything they might regret.”  Clark paled as Lana whispered the last part into the phone.  <br>
<br>
“Yeah,” was all he could get out.<br>
<br>
“Okay, I’ll see you soon,” she chirped, faking a smile for Gabe as he passed by her.  She hung up the phone and Clark felt his stomach sink.  <br>
<br>
He wanted to just run over there, but then there would be the inevitable questions about how he got there.  He took a deep breath and grabbed the truck keys off the key rack.  Heading toward the truck, he only hoped Lana was wrong.<br>
