Lex grinned to himself as Chloe rested her head on his chest.  They had made their way to his bedroom a few hours ago and had pretty much spent the time exhausting themselves with their lovemaking.  <br>
<br>
“Don’t let me fall asleep,” she mumbled before closing her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Okay,” he lied and lightly stroked his fingers over her hair.  He just started to nod off himself when there was a rather abrupt knock at the door.  ‘If that’s my dad, I’m killing him.’  Chloe nodded slightly and rolled over on the bed, snuggling her head up to the pillow instead of Lex.  Lex crawled out of bed and hastily threw a pair of slacks on before going to answer the door.  He opened the door and frowned at his butler.  “What?”  He half-way snapped at the man.<br>
<br>
“Clark Kent is here to see ---”  He trailed off and cleared his throat as he motioned into the bedroom.  Lex squared his jaw.<br>
<br>
“No,” he said and started to close the door.<br>
<br>
“He was quite insistent, sir.  I doubt he’ll simply go away without an explanation.”<br>
<br>
Lex inwardly groaned and Chloe sleepily started to get out of bed, wrapping one of the sheets around herself for cover.  <br>
<br>
‘Don’t,’ Lex thought, hearing her motions behind him.<br>
<br>
‘It’s okay Lex.  It’s almost dinner time.  I should be getting home anyway.’<br>
<br>
‘We have food here,’ Lex argued.  Chloe rolled her eyes and reached down to grab her scattered clothes off the floor.  She flashed a blushing smile to the butler, who seemed to be trying hard not to look at her.<br>
<br>
“Tell him I’ll be down in a little bit,” she said.  The butler nodded and hurried away from the door as if his life depended on it.  Lex closed the door and frowned at her as she slipped into her clothing.<br>
<br>
“I wish you hadn’t done that,” he said.<br>
<br>
“Lex ---”<br>
<br>
“He’s going to want you to leave with him.”<br>
<br>
“I brought my own car, remember?”<br>
<br>
“I know, but he’s still going to want you to leave.”<br>
<br>
“And I *should* be leaving,” Chloe said.  “So, it’s not a big deal.  We’ll see each other at the lab tomorrow morning anyway.”  She smiled at him and then gave him a kiss on the cheek as she reached over to open the door.  Lex caught her wrist and stared almost menacingly at her.  She furrowed her brow.<br>
<br>
‘Mine,’ he thought.  Chloe couldn’t resist rolling her eyes.<br>
<br>
“No,” she stated.  “Remember?  We agreed that we’re just being affected by the chemical and ---”  Lex moved his hand into her hair and Chloe’s eyes drifted shut.  “Lex ---”  In one swift movement, his mouth was on hers, his lips coaxing and persuading hers to open for him.  “Mmm.”  Their tongues wove together and her hands went up to his shoulders.  Lex had just started backing her toward the bed when there was another loud knock on the door.  She pulled away from him and he cursed under his breath as he went to open the door again.<br>
<br>
“What?!”  He yelled in aggravation before seeing who was on the other side of the door.  Chloe’s eyes grew wide and her cheeks started to color when she saw who it was.<br>
<br>
“Clark,” she greeted with an uneasy and forced smile.  “I was just on my way down.”<br>
<br>
Clark desperately wanted to say ‘no you weren’t’, but then he would have to admit to being able to see through doors.  Instead, he settled for scowling at Lex and speaking curly to Chloe.<br>
<br>
“It’s time to go.  Lana and your dad are worried that you’re not home for dinner yet,” he said, extending his hand for her to take it.  She looked at Lex.<br>
<br>
‘Uh-oh.  He’s pissed.’<br>
<br>
‘So?’<br>
<br>
‘How did he get up here so quickly?  The butler just left.’<br>
<br>
‘Adrenaline works wonders on him,’ Lex thought, tongue-in-cheek. <br>
<br>
“Okay, I brought my car,” Chloe said to Clark.  “So, I’ll ---”  She trailed off as she followed Clark’s intent stare at the messed up bed, and then she winced.  ‘Shit.’  Clark looked back and forth between Chloe and Lex and his face drained of any color that had been left in it.  Lex tried to ignore his reaction.<br>
<br>
“No,” Lex said, bringing Clark’s attention back to him.  “She’s not leaving.”  ‘Ever.’<br>
<br>
‘Don’t start,’ Chloe warned him.  She gave a small sigh and then smiled nervously at Clark.  “Lex is being affected --- differently by the chemical and ---” Clark growled, effectively cutting off whatever else Chloe was going to say.  He stared angrily at Lex and took a threatening step toward him.<br>
<br>
“You took advantage of her,” he said.  His volume was low, but the underlying threat was received loud and clear.<br>
<br>
“No, I ---”<br>
<br>
“No, he didn’t Clark,” Chloe interrupted, placing her hand on his arm in an effort to stop him from getting closer to Lex.  Lex saw her hand on Clark’s arm and snapped.<br>
<br>
“Stop touching him!”  He yelled at Chloe.<br>
<br>
Clark was startled by Lex’s outburst and looked at his friend with concern.<br>
<br>
‘Lex, now *really* isn’t the time to start wigging out,’ she thought.  ‘If he thinks you took advantage of me, he’ll kill you.’  She turned her attention to Clark again, but made sure she had removed her hand from his arm.  “Like I said, he’s being affected by the chemical.  It seems to have made him more --- primal.”  Clark looked at the bed and then at her.<br>
<br>
“Did he – did you ---?”<br>
<br>
“He didn’t rape me, Clark.  He wouldn’t do that.”<br>
<br>
“But you said the chemical – and why else would you – you know?”  Clark stammered.  Chloe closed her eyes for a second.<br>
<br>
“We’re both being affected.  You already knew that,” she explained.<br>
<br>
“Yeah, but I didn’t know you were sleeping with him because of it,” Clark argued.  He frowned at his own inability to let the situation go.  It wasn’t Chloe and Lex’s fault that they were being influenced by some chemical, but he had a feeling they would both blame him for not breaking things up earlier once they were cured.  “Come home.  You guys are getting it fixed in the morning, and staying here might not be the best idea given the circumstances.”<br>
<br>
His head whipped around when he heard a feral growl come from Lex’s throat.  He knew that Lex couldn’t hurt him, but that didn’t make him any less intimidating.<br>
<br>
“Lex, think about it,” Clark said.  “You have to let her go home, have some dinner, and get some sleep.  You guys are going to the lab early tomorrow and ---”<br>
<br>
“You think I don’t know what you’re doing, Clark?”  Lex asked.  “You tried to take her away from me.  You’re still trying to take her away from me.”<br>
<br>
‘And here we go again,’ Chloe thought.<br>
<br>
‘Chloe ---”<br>
<br>
“I’m not *yours* Lex.”<br>
<br>
“Yes, you are.”<br>
<br>
“No, I’m not.”<br>
<br>
Clark frowned as he listened to them argue.  Chloe sounded tired and worn down, like they had the same argument several times before – which, Clark realized, they probably had if Lex was being as affected by the chemical as it looked like he was.  <br>
<br>
“Guys ---”<br>
<br>
“Shut up Clark,” they both said at once.  Clark’s eyebrows rose in surprise at their tone and the fact that they had said the same thing at the same time.  It was more than a little disconcerting.  <br>
<br>
“It’s time to go,” he told Chloe again.  <br>
<br>
‘Don’t you see what he’s doing, Chloe?  I swear I’ll kill him if he ---’<br>
<br>
‘If I stay, you have to promise not to hurt him,’ Chloe interrupted.  Lex’s rage boiled up inside of him.  Even though she would be staying, she was essentially choosing Clark over him because she would only be staying to keep Clark out of harm’s reach. <br>
<br>
“I’m not promising anything,” he said sternly.  <br>
<br>
“Lex,” she started to protest, but was suddenly overcome with a wave of dizziness that almost knocked her to the ground.<br>
<br>
“Chloe?”  Lex asked in concern.  He had heard her thoughts trail off, and it worried him.  The concern grew when she seemed to lose her balance and began to fall to the floor.  Clark was closer and he caught her, but when he tried to stand her back up, they both realized that Chloe’s eyes were shut and she was unconscious.  “Chloe?”  Lex repeated with a little more urgency in his voice.  ‘Talk to me.’<br>
<br>
No words came from her mouth and no thoughts came from her mind.  Lex shot Clark a panicked expression.<br>
<br>
“I can’t hear her,” he said almost fearfully.  Clark frowned and carried her to the bed.  He lay her down upon it and then looked at Lex.<br>
<br>
“Maybe it’s just wearing off,” Clark suggested.  <br>
<br>
“She wouldn’t have passed out if it was just wearing off,” Lex said.<br>
<br>
“You don’t know that,” Clark pointed out.<br>
<br>
“If that’s the case, then why didn’t *I* pass out?”  Lex countered.  Clark frowned.  He didn’t have an explanation for that.  Clark noticed it first.  As he watched Chloe’s chest rise and fall, her breathing became progressively slower and shallower.  And then it stopped altogether.<br>
<br>
“She’s stopped breathing,” Clark said in a fearful voice.  Lex called for an ambulance immediately and Clark tried to do mouth to mouth resuscitation on her.  Lex managed to bite back whatever jealousy he was feeling over Clark’s lips touching Chloe’s, reminding himself that he was only trying to save Chloe’s life.  Unfortunately, it didn’t seem to be working<br>
<br>
Lex ran a hand over the back of his neck as he watched on.  It scared him to see her lying there, not moving, not breathing, not thinking.  For the first time since the accident had first occurred, he would have given anything to hear her voice in his head.<br>
