“Chloe?” Clark asked.  At the sound of Clark’s voice, Chloe turned in her chair to face him.  She gave him a wide smile.  <br>
<br>
“Hey, Clark.”<br>
<br>
“Why are you listening to the theme song to The Snorks?”<br>
<br>
“You don’t like The Snorks?”<br>
<br>
“Well – I – I don’t know.  I mean, I haven’t watched cartoons for a long time,” Clark said.  Chloe rolled her eyes. <br>
<br>
“And yet you recognized the theme song,” she pointed out.  Clark opened his mouth to speak, but quickly closed it when he realized he had no rebuttal.  Chloe turned her chair back around to look at the computer.  “And for your information, I used to have a crush on Junior.”<br>
<br>
‘I beg your pardon?’<br>
<br>
“You had a crush on a cartoon character?”<br>
<br>
“You make that sound like it’s a bad thing,” she said.  Clark stared at her in disbelief, not sure of what else to say.  <br>
<br>
‘It is a bad thing.  Who is Junior?’<br>
<br>
‘None of your business,’ Chloe thought.  ‘And speaking of business, is your dad still in the room?’<br>
<br>
Lex looked over and saw his dad still just staring at him with a worried look on his face.<br>
<br>
‘Crap.’<br>
<br>
Chloe started laughing again and Lex squared his jaw.<br>
<br>
‘Okay, Sullivan.  You wanna play?  We’ll play.’<br>
